    <string name="RulesLong">
        Yahtzee is a game based on rolling five dices.
        Players aim to obtain the highest score possible making as much combination as possible, but each one can be made once only.
        These are:
        \n\n
        • Pair(5 points)\n\n
        • Tris(10 points)\n\n
        • Bonus: Achieved whenever during a game your score is greater than 62(35 points)\n\n
        • 4 or 5 straight: Achieved whenever your dice are sortable in ascending order in a group of four or five consecutive numbers(30 and 40 points respectively)\n\n
        • Four dices with same value(20 points)\n\n
        • Full: come nel poker, un tris e una coppia(25 punti)\n\n
        • Yahtzee!: All dices with same value(50 points)\n\n
        • Chance: Achieved the first time you get a combination you just got on a previous roll(25 points)\n
        \nEvery turn, players roll dices up to three times. On second and third roll, it is possible to select the dices you want to roll, to try to achieve a certain combination.
        If there are no available combination at the end of the three rolls, no points are given.
        Wins whoever has the highest total score after 13 turns.\n\nGOOD LUCK!
    </string>
